data: Emilie Passemar Emilie Passemar Associate Professor, Physics epassema@indiana.edu (812) 855-5422 Swain West 224 Postdoc, Los Alamos National Laboratory Postdoc, IFIC, Valencia, Spain Postdoc, ITP, University of Bern, Switzerland Ph.D., University Paris XI, Orsay, France, 2008 theoretical nuclear physics Nuclear theory research My research interests concern the studies of QCD in the non-perturbative domain using dispersive and effective field theory techniques. I am also interested in low energy probes of fundamental symmetries and flavor physics. Learn more about the Nuclear Theory Center
